Minesweeper Roguelike
A dungeon crawling twist on classic Minesweeper. Decend through increasingly harder floors, earn XP, level up, and choose perks that change how you play.

Running the game
    after geting files fro github, go to dist and click on MinesweeperRoguelike.exe

Controls
    left click - Reveal a cell
    Right click - Place/remove a flag
    Middle click - Chord

How it works
    Floors 
        Each run is endles descent through floors. Every floor i a minesweeper bor clear it by reveling all safe cells then descend deeper. Floors ged progressively larger and will have more mines
        
        floor 1 9x9 with around 12% mines
        floor 5 17x17 with around 18% mines
        floor 10+ 20x20+ with up to 30% mines

        Each floor also has a visual theme that changes th color palette:
            Dungeon>Crypt>Cavern>Abyss>Hellgate>Void
    
    Lives
        You start with 3 lives. Hit a mine an you lose one, as simple as that. 

Scoring and XP

    Reveal a safe cell + 1XP +1 Score
    Flag a real mine +3XP no Score
    Clear a floor +50XP + time bonus +50 Score + bonus

    The time bonus for floor cler rewars speed, the faster you finish the more you get

Leveling up
    By geting enough XP you level up. Each level  requires more XP that last. Once you level up you get a new perk.

Perks
    Iron will - Gain +1 extra life immediately
    Eagle Eye - One random safe cell is auto revealed for you at start of the floor
    Cartographer - All four corner cells are reveled for you at the start of each floor
    Scavenger - Correctly flagging a mine grants a bonus XP
    Berserker - Chord clicking reveals one extra unrevealed neighbor
    Sixth Sense - One mine location is briefly flashed at the start of each floor
    Lucky Charm - 15% of mines become harmless duds shown as 💫 when revealed
    Pathfinder-  echances BFS reveal on open areas
